# Vite Best Practices

<core_configuration>
**Essential Vite Configuration Principles:**
- Use TypeScript config files (vite.config.ts) for type safety
- Keep configuration minimal - Vite's defaults are excellent
- Define clear environment modes (development, staging, production)
- Use defineConfig helper for better IDE support
</core_configuration>

## Build Optimization

<build_optimization>
**Critical Build Performance Patterns:**
- Create manual chunks for vendor libraries to improve caching
- Use rollup-plugin-visualizer to analyze bundle size
- Implement tree-shaking optimizations
- Configure proper asset handling
</build_optimization>

```javascript
// vite.config.ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite'
import { visualizer } from 'rollup-plugin-visualizer'

export default defineConfig({
  build: {
    rollupOptions: {
      output: {
        manualChunks: {
          vendor: ['react', 'react-dom'],
          router: ['@tanstack/react-router'],
          query: ['@tanstack/react-query'],
          ui: ['@radix-ui/react-dialog', '@radix-ui/react-dropdown-menu'],
        },
      },
    },
    sourcemap: true,
    minify: 'terser',
    terserOptions: {
      compress: {
        drop_console: true,
        drop_debugger: true,
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [
    // ... other plugins
    visualizer({
      filename: 'dist/stats.html',
      open: true,
      gzipSize: true,
    }),
  ],
})
```

## Development Workflow

<development_workflow>
**Enhanced Development Experience:**
- Configure HMR boundaries properly
- Use proper import resolution
- Set up environment variables correctly
- Implement development-specific optimizations
</development_workflow>

```typescript
// vite.config.ts
export default defineConfig({
  server: {
    port: 3000,
    open: true,
    hmr: {
      overlay: true,
    },
  },
  resolve: {
    alias: {
      '@': path.resolve(__dirname, './src'),
      '@/components': path.resolve(__dirname, './src/components'),
      '@/utils': path.resolve(__dirname, './src/utils'),
    },
  },
  define: {
    __APP_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(process.env.npm_package_version),
  },
})
```

## Plugin Ecosystem

<plugin_ecosystem>
**Essential Plugin Configuration:**
- Use official plugins for React, TypeScript
- Configure Oxlint and Prettier integration
- Set up testing with Vitest
- Add PWA capabilities when needed
</plugin_ecosystem>

```typescript
// vite.config.ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite'
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'
import { TanStackRouterVite } from '@tanstack/router-vite-plugin'

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [
    react(),
    TanStackRouterVite(),
  ],
  test: {
    globals: true,
    environment: 'jsdom',
    setupFiles: ['./src/test/setup.ts'],
  },
})
```

## Environment Management

<environment_management>
**Robust Environment Configuration:**
- Use .env files for different environments
- Validate environment variables at build time
- Implement proper type safety for env vars
- Never expose sensitive data to client
</environment_management>

```typescript
// env.d.ts
interface ImportMetaEnv {
  readonly VITE_API_URL: string
  readonly VITE_APP_TITLE: string
  readonly VITE_ENABLE_ANALYTICS: string
}

interface ImportMeta {
  readonly env: ImportMetaEnv
}

// utils/env.ts
import { z } from 'zod'

const envSchema = z.object({
  VITE_API_URL: z.string().url(),
  VITE_APP_TITLE: z.string().min(1),
  VITE_ENABLE_ANALYTICS: z.enum(['true', 'false']),
})

export const env = envSchema.parse(import.meta.env)
```

## Development Workflow
- Configure server.host for network access during development
- Use server.proxy for API development
- Enable server.cors when needed
- Configure HMR port for container environments

## Asset Handling
- Use import.meta.glob for dynamic imports
- Optimize images with vite-plugin-image-optimizer
- Use ?url suffix for explicit URL imports
- Leverage ?raw suffix for string imports
- Configure assetsInclude for custom asset types

## Module Federation
- Use vite-plugin-federation for micro-frontends
- Keep shared dependencies minimal
- Version shared modules carefully
- Test integration thoroughly

## Path Aliases
```javascript
resolve: {
  alias: {
    '@': path.resolve(__dirname, './src'),
    '@components': path.resolve(__dirname, './src/components'),
    '@hooks': path.resolve(__dirname, './src/hooks'),
    '@utils': path.resolve(__dirname, './src/utils')
  }
}
```

## CSS Handling
- Use CSS modules for component styles
- Configure css.devSourcemap for debugging
- Use PostCSS for autoprefixing
- Leverage css.preprocessorOptions for global variables

## Production Deployment
- Use vite preview to test production builds locally
- Configure base path for subdirectory deployments
- Enable gzip/brotli compression on server
- Use CDN for static assets
- Implement proper cache busting

## SSR Configuration
- Use vite.ssrLoadModule for server-side code
- Configure ssr.external for Node.js modules
- Handle SSR-specific aliases separately
- Use proper build entries for client/server

## Security Considerations
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs
- Use Content Security Policy headers
- Keep Vite and plugins updated
- Audit dependencies regularly
- Configure CORS properly

## Testing Integration
- Use vitest for unit testing (same config as Vite)
- Configure test environment properly
- Use happy-dom or jsdom for DOM testing
- Integrate with CI/CD pipelines

## Common Optimizations
- Prebundle large dependencies
- Use optimizeDeps.include for forced optimization
- Configure commonjsOptions for CJS compatibility
- Minimize experimental features in production

## Debugging Tips
- Use --debug flag for detailed logs
- Enable build.minify: false for debugging
- Use Chrome DevTools for performance profiling
- Monitor bundle size over time
- Track Core Web Vitals metrics
